{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"cf1b294d-b0e5-4bed-a5b4-63f72909656f","content":"Everything after the `--` separator is forwarded to the Microsoft.Testing.Platform runner. The VSTest flags have new equivalents:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test \\\n  --filter \"Category=Integration\" \\\n  -- \\\n  --report-trx \\\n  --coverage \\\n  --coverage-output-format cobertura \\\n  --crashdump \\\n  --hangdump \\\n  --hangdump-timeout 5m\n```\n\n**Flag mapping:**\n\n| VSTest (old) | Microsoft.Testing.Platform (new) |\n|---|---|\n| `--logger trx` | `--report-trx` |\n| `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` | `--coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura` |\n| `--blame-crash` | `--crashdump` |\n| `--blame-hang --blame-hang-timeout 5m` | `--hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5m` |\n\n`--filter` stays **before** `--` as a `dotnet test` argument.\n\n**Required NuGet packages** in the test project:\n\n```xml\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Platform.MSBuild\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CrashDump\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HangDump\" />\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"603fc1c6-9514-4987-918d-80ee9477d21b","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their CI test command from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MSTest runner) on .NET 8. This is a knowledge question about .NET testing tooling migration, not a codebase task.\n\nLet me provide the equivalent command for Microsoft.Testing.Platform.\n\nKey differences when moving to Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n1. `dotnet test` still works but the underlying runner changes\n2. Filter syntax changes: `--filter` becomes `--filter` (same) or `--treenode-filter`\n3. Logger: `--logger trx` becomes `--report-trx`\n\n\n4. Code coverage: `--collect \"Code Coverage\"` becomes `--coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura`\n5. Blame/hang: `--blame-crash` and `--blame-hang` become different flags\n\nWhen using Microsoft.Testing.Platform directly (running the test executable), the CLI flags shift to `--treenode-filter` for filtering, `--report-trx` for TRX output, and `--coverage` with `--coverage-output-format` for coverage reporting.\n\nNow I'm realizing the entry point matters here. With .NET 9, `dotnet test` has been updated to work directly with Microsoft.Testing.Platform, but for .NET 8, you'd typically run the test executable directly or use `dotnet run`. There's also the option of adding `Microsoft.Testing.Platform.MSBuild` to enable the new platform while still using `dotnet test` as the entry point.\n\nWhen running the test project directly with `dotnet run`, the platform accepts flags like `--treenode-filter` or `--filter` for filtering tests, `--report-trx` for TRX output, `--microsoft-code-coverage` with `--coverage-output-format cobertura` for coverage reporting, and `--crashdump` or `--hangdump` with timeout settings for diagnostics. The tricky part is that `dotnet test` with Microsoft.Testing.Platform integration via MSBuild should handle some translation of these flags, but I need to be careful about which syntax applies where. Refining the command syntax for Microsoft.Testing.Platform—when using `dotnet test` with MSBuild integration, the `--filter` flag gets translated properly, so I can use the standard dotnet test syntax with arguments passed after `--` to the platform itself, mapping the old flags like `--logger trx` to `--report-trx` and the code coverage collection to `--coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura`, along with the crash and hang dump options.\n\nTo make this work, I need to ensure the right NuGet packages are installed: `Microsoft.Testing.Platform.MSBuild` to enable the new platform integration, plus the extension packages for TRX reporting, code coverage, crash dumps, and hang dumps.","outputTokens":1679,"requestId":"BD01:4FC4C:1D3F63E:20E4921:6A07C4D3"},"id":"28bf395e-8630-4a7c-b388-9cd0120ffd79","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:14:23.502Z","parentId":"a7f0c38f-35c0-4f2b-9bdd-ec655188c605"}
